10 READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 (1) As used in this section, "the nearest five cent ($0.05) increment" means:
12 (a) Amounts ending in one cent ($0.01) and two cents ($0.02) are rounded
13 down to the nearest ten ($0.10) cents;
14 (b) Amounts ending in three cents ($0.03) and four cents ($0.04) are rounded
15 up to the nearest five ($0.05) cents;
16 (c) Amounts ending in six cents ($0.06) and seven cents ($0.07) are rounded
17 down to the nearest five ($0.05) cents;
18 (d) Amounts ending in eight cents ($0.08) and nine cents ($0.09) are rounded
19 up to the nearest ten ($0.10) cents; and
20 (e) Amounts ending in zero ($0.00) cents and five ($0.05) cents remain
21 unchanged.
22 (2) In order to calculate the breaks in Sections 50 and 51 of this Act:
23 (a) Rounding cash transactions to the nearest five cent ($0.05) increment may
24 occur:
25 1. When pennies are not available to complete resolution of a
26 transaction; and
27 2. On settlement of the final bill of sale, invoice, or fee after all
